WEBVTT

00:03.320 --> 00:04.321
Mr Churchill.

00:04.400 --> 00:06.767
If there are bodies to be buried...

00:06.880 --> 00:08.962
Dig holes.

00:09.120 --> 00:10.360
And dig them deep.

00:10.720 --> 00:11.801
Don't do this in here.

00:11.880 --> 00:13.609
You're taking me away from my baby!

00:13.680 --> 00:14.841
- Freddie!
- Ada!

00:15.920 --> 00:18.730
It wasn't me who shot Freddie Thorne.

00:19.720 --> 00:21.484
He trusts me, I told you that.

00:21.840 --> 00:23.285
I think I know where
the guns are hidden.

00:24.280 --> 00:28.763
I want your word that Thomas Shelby will
not be harmed if the guns are recovered.

00:30.760 --> 00:31.807
(GUNSHOT)

00:31.920 --> 00:34.810
It would be an honour
to work with you, Mr Kimber.

00:35.080 --> 00:38.926
Nobody works "with" me.
People work "for" me.

00:40.200 --> 00:42.407
Black star. What does that mean?

00:42.880 --> 00:46.566
Black star day is the day we take
out Billy Kimber and his men.

00:48.760 --> 00:50.410
Grace...

00:50.480 --> 00:51.527
Will you marry me?

00:52.840 --> 00:53.841
You deserve better.

00:54.400 --> 00:55.401
Is it him?

00:56.880 --> 00:58.928
- CAMPBELL: Where is he?
- He left.

01:00.040 --> 01:01.280
With the barmaid.

01:36.120 --> 01:38.521
(DOOR OPENING)

02:26.000 --> 02:27.126
Service?

02:27.640 --> 02:28.971
(KNOCKING)

02:30.520 --> 02:32.010
We don't open two more hours.

02:32.080 --> 02:33.206
You come back later.

02:34.720 --> 02:35.801
Police.

02:41.480 --> 02:43.084
Inspector Campbell, sir.

02:44.480 --> 02:45.606
Any trouble, sir?

02:46.840 --> 02:48.080
Look...

02:49.120 --> 02:50.281
I know.

02:51.560 --> 02:52.641
I know.

02:54.840 --> 02:55.887
That is,

02:55.960 --> 02:58.486
I'm given to understand by
several of my officers...

02:59.440 --> 03:00.521
(CLEARS TH ROAT)

03:00.600 --> 03:04.207
Several of my officers
that people come here...

03:06.560 --> 03:08.164
That men come here for...

03:09.760 --> 03:10.921
a certain purpose.

03:25.600 --> 03:27.682
Arthur. Arthur, wake up!

03:29.160 --> 03:32.607
Get home, get bathed,
check your kids, check your weapons.

03:35.720 --> 03:36.801
Why?

03:39.440 --> 03:40.566
What's going on?

03:42.640 --> 03:43.846
We're doing it today.

03:47.240 --> 03:53.202
<i># Where secrets lie in the border fires
in the humming wires</i>

03:53.280 --> 03:56.807
<i># Hey man, you know
you're never coming back #</i>

03:56.920 --> 03:58.524
Fetch the wagons, Charlie.

03:59.240 --> 04:00.321
It's today.

04:03.600 --> 04:07.810
<i># On a gathering storm comes
a tall handsome man</i>

04:07.880 --> 04:12.408
<i># In a dusty black coat with
a red right hand #</i>

04:14.320 --> 04:15.401
(MOANING)

04:22.360 --> 04:25.523
(CHILDREN PLAYING)

04:26.000 --> 04:27.001
(GIGGLING)

04:27.240 --> 04:28.571
I'll be there in a minute, mate!

04:28.640 --> 04:29.641
(LOUD KNOCKING)

04:31.760 --> 04:33.762
john, I've told you to keep
the doors locked.

04:34.080 --> 04:35.366
It could have been anyone.

04:35.760 --> 04:36.807
Get dressed.

04:37.440 --> 04:38.487
We're doing it today.

04:38.600 --> 04:40.364
As a matter of fact,
he's doing me today.

04:40.560 --> 04:41.846
Make sure he's done you by 9:00.

04:42.240 --> 04:43.321
You should learn to knock!

04:43.400 --> 04:44.731
It's not a day for knocking.

04:47.720 --> 04:49.722
Dear Lord, make this day pass well.

04:51.680 --> 04:52.920
Let none get hurt,

04:53.520 --> 04:55.648
and make them that do not Shelbys.

04:57.640 --> 04:58.721
Watch john,

04:59.680 --> 05:01.489
'cause he has so many depending on him.

05:03.040 --> 05:04.166
Watch Arthur,

05:05.200 --> 05:08.204
because he's as likely to hurt
himself as anyone else.

05:09.880 --> 05:10.961
Watch Thomas.

05:13.040 --> 05:14.166
I know how he is.

05:15.400 --> 05:17.801
But he does what he does for us.

05:19.960 --> 05:21.086
I think.

05:22.400 --> 05:23.526
Amen.

05:30.240 --> 05:32.208
I used to do that every
morning during the war.

05:32.720 --> 05:34.324
Think'd I'd done it for the last time.

05:35.200 --> 05:36.770
Today will be the last time, Poll.

05:39.040 --> 05:41.441
After today, there'll be
no need for prayers.

05:42.280 --> 05:43.441
We'll be set.

05:46.000 --> 05:47.729
Family meeting, half-ten.

06:01.960 --> 06:03.121
I'm sorry I kept you.

06:03.680 --> 06:04.806
It is so early.

06:05.960 --> 06:07.086
That's all right.

06:07.720 --> 06:09.722
I, I didn't sleep last night.

06:12.920 --> 06:15.969
CHINN: Mr Zhang said that you
are special, special customer.

06:28.320 --> 06:29.401
Do you want to sit?

06:38.560 --> 06:40.210
Do you want to take off your boots?

06:42.080 --> 06:43.161
Yes.

06:52.280 --> 06:53.327
And,

06:53.400 --> 06:54.526
this.

07:00.280 --> 07:01.486
CHINN: So tight.

07:14.400 --> 07:17.290
We can also clean and press
your shirt while we do this.

07:18.320 --> 07:20.846
Ah, that's a very efficient service.

07:22.840 --> 07:25.002
You've never been to a
place like this before?

07:27.680 --> 07:28.761
It's okay.

07:29.080 --> 07:32.527
Sometimes old men who lost
their wives, they come here

07:32.720 --> 07:33.960
all the time.

07:34.680 --> 07:35.727
Old men?

07:36.440 --> 07:37.487
I am so old?

07:37.560 --> 07:39.210
No, I mean...

07:39.720 --> 07:41.722
I am young. anyway---

07:44.280 --> 07:45.770
CHINN: I will make you young as well.

08:46.760 --> 08:47.886
Whore.

09:01.240 --> 09:02.730
<i>CAMPBELL: Dear Grace,</i>

09:03.480 --> 09:06.529
<i>I write this letter to you
with a heavy heart.</i>

09:07.160 --> 09:09.527
<i>I know exactly what you did.</i>

09:10.160 --> 09:11.286
<i>And with whom.</i>

09:12.280 --> 09:15.124
<i>I will not mention any
of it in my report.</i>

09:15.560 --> 09:18.040
<i>However, you should be aware</i>

09:18.120 --> 09:22.523
<i>that I know you gave yourself to
the man who is our sworn enemy.</i>

09:23.200 --> 09:24.770
<i>That is not only treason,</i>

09:26.240 --> 09:29.050
<i>it is disgusting beyond all measure.</i>

09:29.680 --> 09:31.682
<i>Your father would be ashamed of you.</i>

09:32.480 --> 09:35.927
<i>And as for myself,
I am beyond desolation.</i>

09:36.360 --> 09:40.365
<i>You have betrayed every principle
and standard of honour</i>

09:40.440 --> 09:42.204
<i>that was your birth right.</i>

09:43.400 --> 09:45.050
<i>And, for what?</i>

09:46.920 --> 09:48.001
Love.

09:55.520 --> 09:56.931
(PANTING)

10:10.480 --> 10:11.925
Oh, my God, I'm sorry, did I do that?

10:12.960 --> 10:14.121
It's okay.

10:14.600 --> 10:16.364
You are special, special customer.

10:17.920 --> 10:19.206
Would you sit with me for a moment?

10:20.000 --> 10:21.047
Please?

10:23.000 --> 10:24.081
(SIGHS)

10:42.600 --> 10:46.605
(HUSH ED CONVERSATION)

10:55.600 --> 10:56.681
For the suits.

10:57.720 --> 10:59.165
You want to hear something funny?

11:09.560 --> 11:10.686
(SIGHS)

11:11.760 --> 11:13.330
(INAUDIBLE WHISPER)

11:26.400 --> 11:27.481
I am unarmed.

11:32.640 --> 11:34.005
It's curious, Inspector.

11:34.840 --> 11:37.047
I thought you came here
to clean up the city.

11:37.680 --> 11:39.330
Not to sleep with its whores.

11:41.800 --> 11:45.009
You're no different from any other
copper that came before you.

11:46.240 --> 11:49.449
I'm no different from those who would
follow, should I choose to leave.

11:49.840 --> 11:51.410
Oh, you've no reason to stay.

11:52.240 --> 11:53.685
You have what you came for.

11:53.840 --> 11:55.205
Yes, I have what I came for.

11:57.440 --> 12:00.284
I have a meeting with
Mr Winston Churchill at midday.

12:01.680 --> 12:03.250
And, no doubt, he intends to

12:03.320 --> 12:05.800
congratulate me on
finding those stolen guns.

12:06.920 --> 12:10.129
And you still don't know how we
found them, do ya?

12:11.800 --> 12:12.847
Good.

12:12.920 --> 12:14.285
Oh, you got lucky.

12:14.680 --> 12:15.806
Did I?

12:16.000 --> 12:17.081
Yeah.

12:18.200 --> 12:19.850
One thing I have learned

12:21.800 --> 12:24.451
is that you and I are opposites.

12:24.760 --> 12:26.330
But also just the same.

12:28.800 --> 12:30.529
Like an image in a mirror.

12:33.400 --> 12:35.448
We hate people.

12:37.400 --> 12:38.845
And they in turn

12:39.560 --> 12:40.641
hate us.

12:41.800 --> 12:43.131
And fear us.

12:47.880 --> 12:49.405
Before the day is over,

12:50.320 --> 12:52.084
your heart will be broken.

12:53.280 --> 12:54.884
Just the same as mine.

12:58.760 --> 13:00.444
Men like us, Mr Shelby,

13:02.200 --> 13:03.690
will always be alone.

13:05.720 --> 13:07.370
And the love we get,

13:08.680 --> 13:10.125
we will have to pay for.

13:11.880 --> 13:14.360
You forget, Inspector,

13:15.960 --> 13:17.246
I have my family.

13:21.120 --> 13:22.531
Enjoy your day.

13:29.960 --> 13:31.325
(BABY FUSSING)

13:34.680 --> 13:35.920
Oh, little one.

13:36.520 --> 13:38.363
You're much better with him than I am.

13:40.760 --> 13:43.206
He settles quicker with me
because he can't smell the milk.

13:43.560 --> 13:45.130
-(BABY GURGLES)
- You're tired.

13:45.680 --> 13:46.841
Let's put him down.

13:48.760 --> 13:50.922
(AUNT POLLY SHUSH ES THE BABY)

13:52.120 --> 13:53.849
Mine were terrors for the tit.

13:55.000 --> 13:56.126
Both of them.

13:57.560 --> 13:59.324
Well, you never knew
my children, did you?

13:59.720 --> 14:01.324
I was a child myself then.

14:03.880 --> 14:05.245
You never talk about them.

14:06.560 --> 14:08.050
I've no reason to.

14:09.000 --> 14:10.923
(BABY coos)

14:12.000 --> 14:13.809
Heart breaks even when
I think about them.

14:18.240 --> 14:19.321
But, today,

14:20.760 --> 14:22.250
I do have reason to.

14:23.120 --> 14:24.531
Sit down, Ada.

14:33.600 --> 14:35.284
They were three and five years old.

14:37.480 --> 14:43.089
Sally was three, Michael was five,
well, two weeks away from being six.

14:46.080 --> 14:47.525
It was Sunday morning,

14:47.840 --> 14:49.251
I was at church...

14:53.160 --> 14:54.605
"You're not forgiven."

14:55.840 --> 14:56.921
This...

14:57.960 --> 15:00.281
Pinched-faced bitch said to me,
"You're not forgiven."

15:01.040 --> 15:03.884
You see, some sheets I'd
washed and hung on the line

15:03.960 --> 15:05.928
had the name of a hotel in them.

15:06.000 --> 15:07.331
They'd been stolen in a robbery,

15:07.400 --> 15:10.529
and they said some porter
at the hotel had been coshed.

15:11.880 --> 15:14.611
And a woman from around here
told the police about the sheets.

15:14.880 --> 15:17.201
Jealous, you see, about the new sheets.

15:17.560 --> 15:18.891
And when the police came,

15:19.360 --> 15:21.567
they found a spirits still.

15:22.480 --> 15:24.482
Making a few drops of gin.

15:28.440 --> 15:29.601
And for that...

15:32.560 --> 15:34.608
(CRYING) They took my children from me.

15:37.480 --> 15:39.562
And they never told me
where they took them.

15:40.960 --> 15:44.043
And they did it 'cause they could,
and 'cause I was weak.

15:44.720 --> 15:47.121
They will never take your
baby away from you.

15:47.800 --> 15:48.881
Do you know why?

15:50.040 --> 15:51.963
'Cause Tommy won't let them.

15:52.520 --> 15:54.841
'Cause Tommy won't let
them walk all over us.

15:55.680 --> 15:58.843
Now, it is Tommy that has brought
strength and power to this family.

16:00.560 --> 16:01.607
'Cause he knows...

16:02.840 --> 16:05.650
You have to be as bad as them
above in order to survive.

16:08.440 --> 16:11.523
I'm telling you this because
I want you to forgive him.

16:11.640 --> 16:12.766
How can I?

16:13.120 --> 16:15.248
When my Freddie's rotting
in jail because of him.

16:16.760 --> 16:18.842
There's something about
today you need to know.

16:33.640 --> 16:35.688
POLICEMAN: All right, Freddie.
Time to go.

16:35.760 --> 16:37.410
I want to get a message to Campbell.

16:37.600 --> 16:38.601
(SIGHS)

16:38.680 --> 16:40.284
I can't let them move me to Brixton.

16:42.320 --> 16:44.607
If I go to Brixton, they'll kill me.

16:45.160 --> 16:46.241
Freddie...

16:46.920 --> 16:48.763
You're not going to get as
far as Brixton prison.

16:51.440 --> 16:52.521
You're free.

16:53.760 --> 16:55.524
CHURCHILL: I told
the Prime Minister personally

16:55.600 --> 16:57.204
that the guns have been retrieved,

16:57.280 --> 16:59.044
and he actually heard me and listened,

17:00.080 --> 17:02.481
and I'm pretty sure he
gave me a half smile.

17:02.560 --> 17:05.928
He never usually smiles unless
a political opponent dies.

17:06.000 --> 17:07.126
<i>(caucus)</i>

17:07.760 --> 17:11.207
I've plan to put your name
forward in the New Year's Honours List.

17:13.160 --> 17:14.969
- That would be too much, sir.
- Nonsense.

17:15.280 --> 17:16.361
You deserve it.

17:17.079 --> 17:21.165
As I recall, you wrote to me several
times about an undercover operative,

17:21.240 --> 17:22.320
a woman.

17:24.800 --> 17:26.882
Was she involved in the discovery?

17:31.520 --> 17:33.966
Does she deserve some
kind of commendation?

17:40.760 --> 17:41.841
Yes.

17:42.400 --> 17:44.084
She was instrumental.

17:44.640 --> 17:46.961
A truly loyal servant to the Crown.

17:47.400 --> 17:49.482
And that is what the
record should state.

17:50.520 --> 17:54.491
And what of the men who actually
stole the guns? The Peaky...

17:55.160 --> 17:56.207
Blinders, sir.

17:59.400 --> 18:00.925
If we were to make arrests,

18:01.680 --> 18:04.570
the whole thing would end up in
open court, and I know we wish to

18:04.640 --> 18:06.210
keep this matter confidential.

18:06.960 --> 18:08.200
So they'll go free?

18:08.480 --> 18:09.641
Not quite, sir.

18:11.400 --> 18:12.811
See, I have plans

18:13.680 --> 18:14.920
for the Peaky Blinders.

18:19.080 --> 18:20.127
All right?

18:20.320 --> 18:23.290
(EXCITED CONVERSATION)

18:23.960 --> 18:25.644
POLLY: Leave that, boys,
we'll get back to it later.

18:25.720 --> 18:26.846
TOMMY: Right.

18:26.920 --> 18:28.445
We've brought you all here today

18:29.080 --> 18:32.209
'cause this is the day
we replace Billy Kimber.

18:32.680 --> 18:34.921
This is the day we become respectable.

18:35.440 --> 18:42.164
The day we join the official National
Association of Racecourse Bookmakers.

18:43.960 --> 18:45.086
But, first,

18:45.840 --> 18:46.921
we do the dirty work.

18:47.720 --> 18:49.688
Now, you've all known
this day's been coming,

18:49.760 --> 18:51.285
I just haven't told anyone the date.

18:55.400 --> 18:57.289
We're going to the Worcester races.

18:57.720 --> 18:59.722
Track opens at 1:00,
we get there at 2:00.

19:00.240 --> 19:03.005
Now, Kimber thinks we're going there
to help him fight the Lee brothers.

19:04.200 --> 19:05.929
Thanks to the efforts of ourjohn

19:06.520 --> 19:08.409
and his lovely new wife, Esme,

19:08.480 --> 19:10.687
the Lees are now our kin.

19:11.440 --> 19:13.841
I interrupted those efforts this morning
and, uh,

19:14.080 --> 19:17.766
I can assure you all,
john is making great sacrifices

19:18.480 --> 19:19.970
in the cause of peace.

19:20.040 --> 19:21.087
Yea h, all rig ht.

19:21.360 --> 19:24.967
So it'll be us and the Lees against
Kimber's boys.

19:25.680 --> 19:28.160
We take 'em out and leave the bookies.

19:28.880 --> 19:32.202
I'll expect a swift victory which will
send a signal all the way to London

19:32.280 --> 19:37.525
that we believe in letting legitimate
businesses run peacefully.

19:38.280 --> 19:41.409
JOHN:
And, uh, what about Kimber himself?

19:42.280 --> 19:43.805
I'll deal with Kimber.

19:44.320 --> 19:45.481
Any other questions?

19:47.560 --> 19:48.641
Yes.

19:51.680 --> 19:54.445
Does anyone object if I bring
a newcomer to the meeting?

19:59.320 --> 20:00.321
(WHISPERING) Come on.

20:02.840 --> 20:06.640
I'd like to introduce the newest member
of the Shelby clan.

20:09.480 --> 20:11.369
(APPLAUSE)

20:16.880 --> 20:18.166
Welcome home, Ada.

20:19.920 --> 20:20.967
We named him Karl.

20:21.960 --> 20:23.041
After Karl Marx.

20:23.680 --> 20:25.091
Karl bloody Marx.

20:25.160 --> 20:26.446
Let me get a look at him.

20:26.520 --> 20:27.760
Oh, here we go.

20:28.120 --> 20:29.167
ARTHUR: Hey, look!

20:29.920 --> 20:31.649
He looksjust like me, look!

20:32.800 --> 20:35.280
- MAN: Unless his arse looks like you.
- ARTHUR: He's all right.

20:35.920 --> 20:37.081
He's a Shelby.

20:37.800 --> 20:38.881
Well, Ada...

20:40.560 --> 20:41.925
Am I forgiven?

20:42.600 --> 20:45.763
If what Aunt Polly says is true,
you are.

20:47.760 --> 20:48.841
It's true.

20:49.000 --> 20:50.126
(SIGHS)

20:51.920 --> 20:53.081
Thank you, Tommy.

20:58.200 --> 20:59.440
THORNE: So who the hell are you?

20:59.960 --> 21:01.724
POLICEMAN:
Someone who wants to keep his eyes.

21:02.840 --> 21:04.365
They came to my house,

21:05.280 --> 21:07.487
told me to volunteer for this.

21:07.760 --> 21:08.807
Who did?

21:09.920 --> 21:11.001
The Peaky Blinders.

21:18.760 --> 21:20.489
Tommy, Tommy, Tommy.

22:13.680 --> 22:14.681
POLICEMAN 1: Get out of the way!

22:18.200 --> 22:19.361
THORN E: What the bloody hell is that?

22:19.720 --> 22:21.210
Looks like your friends are here.

22:26.360 --> 22:29.364
Stay down on the ground!
Or the next one's for you.

22:33.600 --> 22:34.601
<i>Uh'.!</i>

22:34.680 --> 22:35.966
POLICEMAN 2: Make it look good.

22:36.320 --> 22:38.448
I am sorry about this, comrade.

22:40.080 --> 22:41.081
Holy shit!

22:41.600 --> 22:44.251
- Danny, you're dead!
- No. I've been living in London.

22:44.320 --> 22:45.446
Same thing.

22:46.320 --> 22:47.321
In you get.

22:54.640 --> 22:55.926
All right, lads, listen up.

22:56.000 --> 22:59.368
You have a pint and a chaser,
no more, on the house.

23:00.840 --> 23:03.684
Right. Let's get pouring.

23:04.720 --> 23:06.484
Do you have the enclosure tickets?

23:06.640 --> 23:08.449
And the registered bookkeepers
on the track?

23:08.840 --> 23:09.921
In me coat.

23:11.480 --> 23:12.891
You did a good job, Grace.

23:14.000 --> 23:15.001
- Much.
- Much.

23:16.440 --> 23:17.805
(CLEARS TH ROAT)

23:18.200 --> 23:19.531
Next family meeting,

23:20.120 --> 23:21.246
I'll make sure you're there.

23:22.680 --> 23:23.841
If I were family.

23:24.480 --> 23:25.845
But I'm not.

23:27.120 --> 23:28.281
That could change.

23:29.720 --> 23:31.085
- Tommy...
- We'll talk about it more

23:31.160 --> 23:32.650
when I get back, all right?

23:32.720 --> 23:33.767
When will you be back?

23:34.040 --> 23:35.963
Oh, is this how it's gonna be, eh?

23:37.040 --> 23:38.690
You waiting at home for me,

23:39.200 --> 23:40.531
saying, "What time do you call this?"

23:42.280 --> 23:43.850
The barrel needs changing.

23:47.200 --> 23:51.000
Go on, Tom. Go out the back,
give her a good seeing to before we go.

23:59.360 --> 24:00.407
All right?

24:01.200 --> 24:03.202
Hey, Grace, I wasjoking.

24:03.480 --> 24:06.131
-(KNOCKING AT DOOR)
- MAN: Tommy, we need more mild.

24:06.280 --> 24:08.009
Just help yourselves!

24:10.600 --> 24:11.726
Tommy, the truth is...

24:12.400 --> 24:14.164
When you come back from the races,
I won't be here.

24:16.000 --> 24:17.081
What are you talking about?

24:19.320 --> 24:20.446
All right, look.

24:20.520 --> 24:23.364
Grace, I know you weren't born
to be with a man like me.

24:25.960 --> 24:27.450
But I'm turning things around.

24:28.200 --> 24:31.647
When I get back here tonight,
I will have

24:32.360 --> 24:36.490
one of the biggest legal race track
syndicates in the country.

24:38.400 --> 24:40.971
I'm gonna close down
some of that other stuff.

24:43.200 --> 24:44.406
Maybe open a club.

24:45.960 --> 24:47.644
Hey, back in London.

24:49.240 --> 24:50.366
And another thing,

24:53.280 --> 24:54.884
you have a contract of employment.

24:55.680 --> 24:58.081
With a real limited company.

24:58.680 --> 24:59.761
You remember?

25:00.400 --> 25:01.970
I remember everything, Tommy.

25:02.400 --> 25:03.970
I am going to a make a success of this.

25:05.440 --> 25:07.044
I am going to a make a success of it.

25:07.440 --> 25:08.601
- I am.
- I know.

25:09.240 --> 25:10.366
I know.

25:11.880 --> 25:13.644
I'm not talking about marriage.

25:14.640 --> 25:15.721
I'm so...

25:17.560 --> 25:18.641
We know each other.

25:19.120 --> 25:20.281
We can talk.

25:21.200 --> 25:22.281
We're the same.

25:23.080 --> 25:26.129
Tommy,
I've done something terrible to you.

25:29.200 --> 25:31.521
Right. Tell him what you just told me.

25:32.160 --> 25:34.128
Just heard there's two vans driving up
the Stratford Road.

25:34.400 --> 25:36.687
JEREMIAH: An old corporal of mine said
he recognised some of the men.

25:36.760 --> 25:38.091
He said it's the Kimber boys.

25:38.440 --> 25:39.521
And they're heading this way.

25:46.680 --> 25:47.727
(DOOR SLAMS)

25:47.800 --> 25:48.926
TOMMY: Ada! Wake up!

25:49.000 --> 25:51.890
You and the baby, get into the bullring
where there's lots of people.

25:51.960 --> 25:54.167
- What's going on?
- We've been fucking betrayed.

25:54.280 --> 25:56.886
Someone let slip.
Kimber's men are on their way here.

25:57.280 --> 25:59.601
- Yeah, but you can handle them, Tommy.
- TOMMY: It's just us.

25:59.720 --> 26:02.041
All the Lees are on their way to
Worcester, we're outnumbered.

26:02.640 --> 26:03.641
(SCREAMING) Fuck!

26:03.720 --> 26:06.451
Who else knew today was the day
you were moving on Kimber?

26:06.800 --> 26:09.201
You said you kept it a secret.
Who else did you tell?

26:12.800 --> 26:15.326
There's only one thing can blind
a man as smart as you, Tommy.

26:16.200 --> 26:17.247
Love.

26:17.440 --> 26:18.601
It's that barmaid.

26:21.560 --> 26:23.244
POLLY: I'll deal with Grace.

26:24.000 --> 26:26.651
If you set eyes on her again,
you might kill her.

26:43.920 --> 26:45.046
POLLY: Going for good?

26:45.320 --> 26:46.401
GRACE: I heard there was trouble.

26:47.040 --> 26:48.724
Instinct's a funny thing.

26:50.440 --> 26:53.091
See, normally I can tell about a person,
but with you...

26:53.200 --> 26:54.929
Look, the fighting's about to begin.

26:55.360 --> 26:57.362
- We should get out of here.
- We know who you are.

27:00.960 --> 27:02.086
Tommy knows as well.

27:03.160 --> 27:05.401
Turned out that copper as good as
told him this morning.

27:05.640 --> 27:07.847
But I wanted to hear it
from your own lips.

27:13.640 --> 27:15.449
I am an agent of the Crown.

27:15.640 --> 27:18.928
I have the power to arrest
and the right to use force.

27:19.120 --> 27:22.044
So please, step out of my way.

27:22.120 --> 27:25.841
Like I say, instinct's a funny thing.
You fell for Tommy for real, didn't you?

27:27.560 --> 27:28.800
This gun is loaded.

27:29.680 --> 27:30.806
I'm not afraid of you.

27:31.800 --> 27:33.040
I feel sorry for you.

27:34.160 --> 27:35.286
Slip of a thing.

27:36.240 --> 27:38.163
Thought you'd come in here and stitch us
all up.

27:38.240 --> 27:40.971
I mean, we've had some copper's narks
in here, but you...

27:41.840 --> 27:42.921
You're the queen of them all.

27:45.920 --> 27:47.001
So who are you?

27:49.080 --> 27:50.525
Rich girl, I'd guess.

27:51.640 --> 27:54.883
Unionist. Ulster Volunteer.

27:56.320 --> 28:01.804
You thought, "Fenians, communists,
low people...

28:02.640 --> 28:05.689
"They're all the same. Scum."

28:06.800 --> 28:07.961
Then you met Tommy.

28:13.440 --> 28:16.284
I'll fight you with my fists
and show you how a rich girl fights.

28:17.240 --> 28:18.890
I'm from a tough family, too.

28:26.280 --> 28:27.486
Nah.

28:29.680 --> 28:31.170
We women have more sense.

28:33.080 --> 28:34.605
Why don't you pour us both a drink?

28:48.000 --> 28:49.161
So am I right?

28:53.280 --> 28:54.645
Did you fall for Tommy?

29:03.560 --> 29:04.641
Yes, I did.

29:05.040 --> 29:06.166
Then I pity you.

29:07.600 --> 29:09.170
You think he'll try to kill me?

29:10.240 --> 29:11.321
That's too soft.

29:11.480 --> 29:12.925
- Soft?
- Soft.

29:13.960 --> 29:15.007
Like you.

29:15.800 --> 29:17.768
You saved his life the night
the coppers came.

29:19.280 --> 29:21.203
That's why we're drinking, not fighting.

29:22.760 --> 29:23.966
We owe you.

29:30.160 --> 29:31.286
What was he like?

29:32.640 --> 29:33.721
Before France?

29:35.520 --> 29:38.046
He laughed. A lot.

29:40.040 --> 29:41.804
He wanted to work with horses.

29:44.360 --> 29:45.441
He won medals?

29:45.520 --> 29:46.601
Threw them in the cut.

29:48.240 --> 29:50.447
Not a single man came back the same.

29:52.880 --> 29:55.770
You know, after all this is over,

29:57.560 --> 29:58.721
he might forgive you.

29:59.600 --> 30:00.681
He might take you in.

30:01.040 --> 30:02.121
Can never tell with men.

30:02.920 --> 30:06.288
They go for whoever their dicks point at
and there's no changing their minds.

30:06.640 --> 30:07.846
But I should tell you something.

30:09.960 --> 30:11.405
I will never forgive you.

30:13.040 --> 30:14.530
Or accept you.

30:15.480 --> 30:16.527
Or take you in.

30:18.360 --> 30:21.091
And it's me who runs the business
of the heart in this family.

30:22.960 --> 30:24.564
And as far as I'm concerned,

30:25.520 --> 30:27.329
you're a snitch from the parish.

30:28.680 --> 30:30.842
And if you're not gone from this city
by tomorrow,

30:32.480 --> 30:33.766
I'll kill you myself.

30:39.960 --> 30:41.041
Now go.

30:55.440 --> 30:57.329
Maybe what really upsets you

30:57.960 --> 30:59.928
is the thought that one day
you might lose him.

31:12.600 --> 31:15.251
Tommy! We've had word
from Nipper at Hay Mills,

31:15.320 --> 31:16.606
and he says
the police are letting them through.

31:18.000 --> 31:19.570
And how come all our police
have disappeared?

31:19.640 --> 31:22.291
'Cause it was the police who told
Kimber about the plan.

31:22.440 --> 31:23.521
And who told the police?

31:23.600 --> 31:27.400
You know what, john?
For all I think I'm the smart one,

31:27.480 --> 31:29.323
I'm guessing it was me.

31:32.200 --> 31:33.281
TOMMY: All right, men.

31:36.400 --> 31:39.688
You were mostly in the war, so you know
that battle plans always change

31:39.760 --> 31:41.922
and get fucked up, well here it is.

31:42.240 --> 31:43.605
Things have changed.

31:43.800 --> 31:46.929
We fight them here. Today. Alone.

31:47.160 --> 31:48.730
Now, they're gonna come for the pub,

31:48.840 --> 31:50.922
they're gonna try
and break us up for good.

31:51.240 --> 31:53.481
And we'll have no help
from the law today.

31:55.080 --> 31:57.287
That pub there is called The Garrison!

31:57.440 --> 31:58.965
Well, now it really is one.

31:59.320 --> 32:01.527
And it belongs to us! Right?

32:01.600 --> 32:02.965
ALL: Right!

32:03.040 --> 32:04.121
How many are there?

32:04.320 --> 32:06.288
Jeremiah said two Reilly vans.

32:07.160 --> 32:09.208
So I reckon we're outnumbered
three to one.

32:09.280 --> 32:10.361
ARTHUR: Ah, fuck.

32:10.440 --> 32:12.966
But it's us, boys, it's us!

32:13.040 --> 32:15.122
The Small Heath rifles.

32:15.400 --> 32:17.164
Never lost a fight yet, did we?

32:17.240 --> 32:18.605
- ALL: No!
- All right!

32:18.680 --> 32:23.242
Jeremiah, I know you vowed to God
to never pick up a weapon again.

32:23.320 --> 32:26.688
But can you ask him from me
if you can help us today.

32:28.040 --> 32:30.042
God says he done a deal
with Small Heath, sir.

32:30.120 --> 32:31.246
Good man!

32:31.320 --> 32:33.243
Arthur, Scudboat, you take the flanks.

32:33.320 --> 32:34.606
- Just like at St Marie.
- Sure.

32:34.680 --> 32:35.727
Curly.

32:35.800 --> 32:37.928
If any Shelby man dies here today,

32:38.320 --> 32:40.129
you bury us side by side.

32:41.200 --> 32:43.646
All right. We've about ten minutes.

32:43.920 --> 32:45.285
Make your peace with whoever.

32:49.680 --> 32:51.569
MOSS: We've heard a report
of a large group of men

32:51.640 --> 32:53.642
in vehicles heading towards the city.

32:53.720 --> 32:55.484
Most of them are
known to the police, sir.

32:55.880 --> 32:59.282
Uh. We think a gang fight's
about to break out.

32:59.960 --> 33:02.247
CAMPBELL: I want all officers
and constables

33:02.320 --> 33:04.209
stood down in the following areas.

33:04.960 --> 33:06.041
Bo rd esley,

33:06.320 --> 33:08.561
Small Heath, Shard End, Greet,

33:09.400 --> 33:11.164
-and Hay Mills.
- Stood down, sir?

33:11.240 --> 33:13.368
Immediately.
And the vehicles approaching the city

33:13.440 --> 33:16.125
-should not be impeded.
- What the hell is going on?

33:16.880 --> 33:18.325
Let dog eat dog.

33:19.880 --> 33:22.247
Let the beasts devour each other.

33:23.720 --> 33:25.848
And then we shall pick the bones.

33:40.520 --> 33:41.601
HARRY: She's gone, then?

33:48.960 --> 33:51.645
You're not accustomed to not getting
what you want, are you, Tommy?

33:55.080 --> 33:57.048
You wanted my pub, and you took it.

34:07.720 --> 34:09.449
You got a fair price.

34:12.719 --> 34:15.087
What I got was an ultimatum.

34:15.840 --> 34:17.284
Like you give to everybody.

34:17.760 --> 34:19.250
Do it, or else.

34:20.639 --> 34:22.449
And yet, it's funny,

34:23.440 --> 34:27.047
everybody around here,
they want you to win this battle.

34:30.000 --> 34:31.081
I think what it is,

34:31.600 --> 34:34.967
you're bad men, but you're our bad men.

34:39.239 --> 34:40.400
Will you go looking for her?

34:45.159 --> 34:46.321
She's in the past.

34:50.360 --> 34:51.804
The past is not my concern.

34:56.120 --> 34:58.441
The future is no longer
my concern either.

34:58.520 --> 35:00.090
What is your concern, Tommy?

35:02.920 --> 35:04.001
TOMMY: One minute.

35:07.680 --> 35:09.409
<i>TOMMY". The soldier's minute.</i>

35:11.360 --> 35:12.771
In a battle, that's all you get.

35:16.240 --> 35:18.083
One minute of everything at once.

35:22.640 --> 35:24.324
Anything before is nothing.

35:27.400 --> 35:28.481
Everything after,

35:29.640 --> 35:30.801
nothing.

35:33.240 --> 35:34.605
Nothing in comparison

35:35.920 --> 35:37.046
to that one minute.

35:43.440 --> 35:45.249
HARRY: Didn't you get enough minutes
over there?

35:52.080 --> 35:53.491
Seems not, doesn't it?

35:55.600 --> 35:56.761
(DOOR OPENS)

35:57.400 --> 35:58.606
Tommy, they're here!

36:44.400 --> 36:46.721
Get your weapons out, boys,
and load 'em up.

36:50.960 --> 36:52.405
Take your time.

36:53.560 --> 36:56.404
Hold 'em up in the air so's they can see
what we've got.

37:04.880 --> 37:07.963
JOHN: All guns and no balls,
right, Billy boy?

37:16.960 --> 37:20.123
So what do we do now?
just give the order.

37:43.720 --> 37:46.929
The men that have arrived in Garrison
Lane, they're armed with rifles.

37:49.200 --> 37:50.326
Did you hear me?

37:51.080 --> 37:54.289
Their methods of self-destruction
are not my concern.

37:54.760 --> 37:58.481
Well, we've outside reports of
machine gun fire in Saltley.

37:59.120 --> 38:01.521
It's the ravings of an old soldier
with shell shock.

38:02.200 --> 38:06.569
We only found 24 of those 25 Lewis guns.
If they were to get use of one...

38:11.120 --> 38:16.286
You know, uh... When you came here
from Belfast, I was overjoyed.

38:17.120 --> 38:20.408
I was sick of this force,
and I was sick of all the corruption.

38:20.920 --> 38:23.890
When you made that speech
about cleaning this place up,

38:24.400 --> 38:26.402
I gave a little cheer inside.

38:29.480 --> 38:32.404
You said it was the devil's work
to look the other way.

38:32.520 --> 38:35.524
I am not looking the other way,
Sergeant Moss.

38:35.880 --> 38:38.531
I am looking directly
at the events of the day!

38:39.000 --> 38:40.650
And I like what I see.

38:48.560 --> 38:50.324
TOMMY: It doesn't have
to be like this, Kimber.

38:50.640 --> 38:52.688
(SCOFFS) It's too late for all that.

38:53.040 --> 38:55.168
You've bit off more than you can chew,
you little toe-rag,

38:55.240 --> 38:57.208
and now I'm going
to take over this shithole.

38:57.320 --> 39:00.802
Well... If we have to use guns...

39:02.160 --> 39:04.288
Let's use proper guns!

39:10.360 --> 39:13.842
Sergeant Thorne reporting for duty, sir.

39:16.680 --> 39:18.842
You were saying something
about being out-gunned?

39:34.400 --> 39:35.447
ADA: Move!

39:38.040 --> 39:39.246
(BABY CRYING)

39:39.320 --> 39:40.321
What are you doing?

39:40.440 --> 39:42.408
I believe you boys
call this "no man's land".

39:42.760 --> 39:44.489
- Ada!
- Shut up and listen.

39:44.560 --> 39:46.562
- THORNE: Have you lost your mind?
- I said shut up!

39:46.640 --> 39:48.847
(BABY CRYING)

39:49.480 --> 39:53.690
Now, most of you were in France.
So you all know what happens next.

39:54.920 --> 39:56.684
I've got brothers and a husband here,

39:57.000 --> 39:58.968
but you've all got
somebody waiting for you.

39:59.760 --> 40:01.967
Now, I'm wearing black in preparation.

40:04.520 --> 40:06.329
I want you to look at me.

40:06.560 --> 40:08.403
(BABY CONTINUES CRYING)

40:09.400 --> 40:11.607
I want you all to look at me!

40:12.480 --> 40:14.209
We'll be wearing black for you.

40:16.040 --> 40:17.280
Think about them.

40:18.280 --> 40:19.930
Think about them right now,

40:21.200 --> 40:22.884
and fight if you want to,

40:23.600 --> 40:25.523
but that baby ain't moving anywhere.

40:27.320 --> 40:28.765
And neither am I.

40:34.200 --> 40:35.486
She's right, you know.

40:36.800 --> 40:38.768
Why should all you men die?

40:39.480 --> 40:41.369
It should just be them whose caused it!

40:45.760 --> 40:47.410
ADA: (ECHOING) Tommy, come here!

40:48.960 --> 40:51.930
MAN: Don't shoot!
ARTHUR: You're all right, Son!

40:52.080 --> 40:53.684
- ARTHUR: You're all right.
- THORNE: Ada, move away!

40:55.400 --> 40:56.640
THORN E: Don't shoot!

40:56.720 --> 40:58.961
(IN DISTINCT YELLING)

40:59.120 --> 41:01.009
ARTHUR: Hold your guns up!

41:02.760 --> 41:04.410
TOMMY: Enough!

41:12.120 --> 41:14.771
Kimber and me fought
this battle one-on-one.

41:16.480 --> 41:17.686
It's over.

41:23.680 --> 41:25.444
Go home to your families.

41:56.200 --> 41:59.568
Scudboat, Curly, pick him up.

42:19.680 --> 42:22.889
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

42:24.360 --> 42:26.169
(CAMPBELL SIGHS)

42:30.480 --> 42:33.962
GRACE: I want to ask you one question.
Then I'll leave.

42:35.000 --> 42:38.402
Tommy knows who I am.
What did you say to him?

42:39.920 --> 42:41.809
What did you say to him?

42:46.760 --> 42:48.762
I told him...

42:49.760 --> 42:52.843
That his heart would be broken
before the day was over.

42:55.600 --> 43:00.481
So it seems...
You've broken two hearts, Grace.

43:04.400 --> 43:06.448
As well as my own.

43:10.040 --> 43:14.011
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

43:16.200 --> 43:16.530
(TOMMY SCREAMING)

43:16.520 --> 43:17.248
(TOMMY SCREAMING)

43:17.320 --> 43:19.641
MAN 1: That's it, Tommy, that's it!
Fight it, Tommy!

43:19.800 --> 43:22.406
- TOMMY: No!
- ARTHUR: Take it! Take it!

43:22.480 --> 43:24.369
- JEREMIAH: Hold him still!
- MAN 2: That's it, lad!

43:24.680 --> 43:26.284
- ARTHUR: Come on! Come on!
-(SCREAMING)

43:27.040 --> 43:30.328
(SCREAMING)

43:30.800 --> 43:34.282
- There! I still have the knack.
- TOMMY: Argh!

43:35.520 --> 43:38.490
-(PANTING)
- ARTHUR: Have a drink.

43:41.560 --> 43:43.847
- All right. Deep breath!
-(GRUNTING IN PAIN)

43:44.600 --> 43:46.728
That's it. It's done!

43:47.920 --> 43:50.446
(PANTING)

44:09.800 --> 44:13.441
Now we can bury him properly,
in the grave we dug for him.

44:16.120 --> 44:20.887
Yeah. It's high on a hill.
He'll like that.

44:29.560 --> 44:31.642
- To Danny Whizz-Bang.
- Danny.

44:31.720 --> 44:33.643
May we all die twice.

44:37.080 --> 44:38.764
To Danny Whizz-Bang.

44:42.040 --> 44:44.122
Danny Whizz-Bang.

44:51.240 --> 44:53.083
(UNDER BREATH) Danny Whizz-Bang.

45:01.800 --> 45:06.647
(SIGHS) Come on.
The day is ours. Let's celebrate.

45:23.280 --> 45:25.169
(FOOTSTEPS)

45:30.360 --> 45:33.842
CAMPBELL: Well, who won?

45:35.080 --> 45:39.642
A Mr William Kimber has been found dead.
A gunshot wound.

45:40.640 --> 45:46.044
So, uh, I'm guessing that means
the Peaky Blinders won, sir.

45:48.320 --> 45:51.642
Also, the communist agitator,
Freddie Thorne,

45:51.720 --> 45:55.202
was taken from his transport
by armed men.

45:56.760 --> 45:59.604
Since there were no officers
on the street at the time,

45:59.680 --> 46:03.969
following your orders, he managed
to escape easily and he's now at large.

46:05.400 --> 46:08.404
The, er, prison officers said they
recognised the men.

46:08.480 --> 46:11.086
They were Peaky Blinders as well, sir.

46:12.760 --> 46:15.127
I mean, we could go down there
and make a few arrests,

46:15.200 --> 46:17.487
but no one will have seen anything.

46:18.520 --> 46:21.569
And there were no officers
there to witness, so...

46:23.080 --> 46:25.401
The Shelbys'll get away with murder.

46:26.240 --> 46:28.208
Just like they always have.

46:29.760 --> 46:33.242
Some things never change, eh, sir?

46:37.320 --> 46:41.041
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

46:44.920 --> 46:48.003
(LOUD CHATTER)

46:50.640 --> 46:54.122
(LOUD CHATTER CONTINUES)

47:00.520 --> 47:04.605
- ARTHUR: A toast! To Shelby, Limited!
- MEN: To Shelby, Limited!

47:10.240 --> 47:12.402
He's got sons.
Should we find work for them?

47:13.120 --> 47:15.282
- No. Let 'em be.
-(CAR DOOR SLAMS)

47:15.400 --> 47:18.244
Let them find ordinary work.
Like ordinary men.

48:03.320 --> 48:05.721
Could you put me through
to Mr Churchill, please?

48:08.200 --> 48:11.682
Yes, sir. Sir...

48:12.520 --> 48:16.002
I have made a decision about my future.

48:30.120 --> 48:32.407
TOMMY: Everyone's leaving town.

48:33.440 --> 48:35.249
- Tommy, you're hurt.
- I'm fine.

48:38.080 --> 48:40.890
- What exactly can I say?
- I don't know, Grace.

48:43.880 --> 48:47.362
- If I tell you who I really am?
- I think I know who you are.

48:48.480 --> 48:50.767
- Okay.
- You know who I am?

48:50.960 --> 48:52.689
Circumstance is not important.

48:52.760 --> 48:56.162
-(SCOFFS) Circumstance.
- Is all it is.

48:58.280 --> 49:01.762
- Just uniform.
- Yeah.

49:07.320 --> 49:09.482
Someday I will throw
this gun in the canal.

49:10.240 --> 49:12.163
Why not now?

49:22.360 --> 49:24.522
Here it comes, Tommy.

49:27.000 --> 49:29.128
I love you.

49:30.920 --> 49:33.844
And there it goes, Grace.

49:35.080 --> 49:36.809
Away it goes.

49:38.280 --> 49:40.328
You can say it as much as you like.

49:42.960 --> 49:45.008
But there's no chance.

49:57.920 --> 50:01.083
I'll be in London one week.
This address.

50:01.520 --> 50:03.568
Finish your business here and join me.

50:06.680 --> 50:08.603
I have an idea.

50:21.040 --> 50:22.724
(DOOR OPENS)

50:25.160 --> 50:26.889
- ARTHUR: There he is.
-jOHN: Tommy!

50:27.040 --> 50:28.769
Drink?

50:33.360 --> 50:35.089
Not whisky.

50:38.000 --> 50:41.004
If you check behind the bar...
(CLEARS THROAT)

50:41.720 --> 50:44.451
You will find a bottle of champagne.

50:54.320 --> 50:55.481
One she bought?

51:02.760 --> 51:04.762
Today was a good day.

51:08.600 --> 51:10.602
All of Kimber's men were busy here.

51:11.560 --> 51:14.803
So the Lee boys took all the pitches
at the Worcester races.

51:17.800 --> 51:19.802
Couldn't have gone better
if we planned it.

51:20.680 --> 51:22.523
TOMMY: The Shelby Brothers, Limited,

51:23.040 --> 51:28.649
are now the third largest legal
racetrack operation in the country.

51:28.720 --> 51:29.767
ARTHUR: Cheers.

51:29.840 --> 51:32.844
Only the Sabinis and the Solomons
are bigger than us, boys.

51:37.840 --> 51:39.922
TOMMY: And all my family
is here to celebrate.

51:41.960 --> 51:43.769
(CHAMPAGN E CORK POPS)

51:44.880 --> 51:46.928
To Shelby Brothers, Limited!

51:47.320 --> 51:49.926
- ARTHUR: Shelby!
- Cheers!

51:50.520 --> 51:52.648
(MEN GROANING)

51:55.320 --> 51:56.924
(GLASS CLIN KING)

52:01.520 --> 52:02.646
(EXHALES)

52:06.680 --> 52:08.091
There'll be others.

52:16.680 --> 52:18.728
To the others.

52:19.360 --> 52:21.931
-(GLASS CLIN KING)
- TOMMY: All of them.

52:51.080 --> 52:53.686
(TYPEWRITER KEYS CLACKING)

52:53.760 --> 52:55.728
<i>TOMMY: "Dear Grace,</i>

52:55.800 --> 52:58.280
<i>"without a secretary,
I write my own letters.</i>

52:58.760 --> 53:00.330
<i>"And I write without lies.</i>

53:01.760 --> 53:04.047
<i>"I learnt long ago to hate my enemies,</i>

53:05.280 --> 53:07.169
<i>"but I've never loved one before.</i>

53:12.320 --> 53:14.527
<i>"The idea of New York is interesting,</i>

53:15.400 --> 53:19.325
<i>"but I have worked so hard for this day.
For this victory.</i>

53:19.760 --> 53:24.049
<i>"I have responsibilities here,
for people I need to protect,</i>

53:25.000 --> 53:26.729
<i>"and people who I love.</i>

53:29.440 --> 53:32.569
<i>"Before the war, when I had
an important decision to make,</i>

53:32.960 --> 53:36.726
<i>"I used to flip a coin.
Perhaps that is what I will do again.</i>

53:39.920 --> 53:42.082
<i>"Polly tells me you
fell in love for real,</i>

53:42.200 --> 53:44.567
<i>"and Polly is never wrong
about matters of the heart.</i>

53:48.760 --> 53:51.240
<i>"I will give you my decision
within three days.</i>

53:54.520 --> 53:57.091
<i>"All my love, Tommy Shelby."</i>

54:13.600 --> 54:17.082
(TRAIN ROARING)

54:32.800 --> 54:34.529
(GUNSHOT)

